This project investigates the global energy efficiency trends and its effects on CO2 emissions. 
Throughout the lens of economic analysis, the project aims to answer the question â€“ can policies aiming to increase energy efficiency assist the environment?

Key Findings:

Post-Soviet countries have experienced rapid improvements in energy efficiency.

Energy efficiency dynamics differ between developing and developed countries.

The UK emerges as a leading energy-efficient economy.

Significant regional heterogeneity exists in energy efficiency between England and Wales.

Renewable energy adoption and human capital are found to have a significant positive impact on energy efficiency.
